'''''Diary of a Mad Band''''' is the second [[studio album]] from [[United States|American]] [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] group [[Jodeci]], released in 1993 on [[Uptown Records]] and distributed through [[MCA Records]].

==Release and reception==
{{Album ratings
| rev1 = [[Allmusic]]
| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name="AllmscRvw">{{cite web|title=allmusic ((( Diary of a Mad Band > Review )))|url=http://allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&sql=10:kjfoxqlgldje~T1|publisher=''[[Allmusic]]''|accessdate=2010-03-31}}</ref>
| rev2 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''
| rev2Score = (B+)<ref name="EWRvw">{{cite web|first=Dimitri|last=Ehrlich|title=MUSIC REVIEW: Diary of a Mad Band (1993) - Jodeci|publisher=''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''|date=1993-12-24|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,309051,00.html|accessdate=2010-04-10}}</ref>
}}
Dimitri Ehrlich of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' believed the album at times bested the group's first, stating that the songs on their sophomore effort "often transcend the formulaic histrionics that marred their debut."<ref name="EWRvw"></ref>

